OK, I'm no longer sure that this is a VE bug.

Here is what happened. 
I am using a JDK1.5 library and also running under JDK1.5 in my project.
I have eclipse's compile settings set to produce 1.4 class files.
When I submitted this bug I first checked by 
(a) switching to JDK1.4 to run the code 
and 
(b) removing the 1.5 library from the list of jars.

However, on further testing this does not appear to be sufficient.
Basically, I was able to make the problem go away by switching the eclipse
compile settings to produce 1.3 class files.

VE tires to compile (using the JDT) the JavaJet template for generating an
anonymouse event code snippet... but when it tries to load the generated class
it gets this Unsupported major.minor version 49.0.   This will typically happen
if you are trying to load a 1.5 class on a 1.4 JRE???

Is the PrefPage->Java->Compiler complinace level at 1.4?
What ventor is the JRE from (Sun??)
What JRE do you use for the Project of your visual class?

* You will have to clean the JavaJet directory again to let VE reCompile it.

Right now VE will use the default JRE settings (which are typically used for the
target projects/plugins).

VE consumes the classes withing the IDE, and should be using the IDE's settings.
